$ PowerShell cmdLet copy-item

{ Copy directories

  In order to recursively copy a directory into a directory, the `-recurse` parameter is required.

  The command to copy a directory depends on whether the destination directory already exists or if the command should create it.

  { Create destination directory

    If the destination directory does not exist, the following will create it (`dest-dir`):
code {
copy-item   -recurse  src    dest
code }

  }
  { Destination directory already exists

    If the destination directory already exists, there are two approaches to copy a directory.
code {
copy-item   -recurse  src    dest
copy-item   -recurse  src/*  dest
code }

   The first command will create a subdirectory named `src` below `dest` while the second command does not create such a `src` directory. 

  }

}
{ Aliases

 `copy` and `cp` are → Windows/PowerShell/language/alias[aliases] for `copy-item`.
 These apparantly resemble the → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[`cmd.exe`] command → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/copy[`copy`] and the
 Shell command → Linux/shell/commands/cp[`cp`].

}

